# Package manager — Bun only

This monorepo uses **Bun**. Each app has its own `package.json` in `backend/` and `frontend/`.

## Commands

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install deps | `bun install` |
| Add dependency | `bun add <pkg>` |
| Add dev dependency | `bun add -d <pkg>` |
| Remove | `bun remove <pkg>` |
| Run script | `bun run <script>` |
| Run TS file | `bun <file.ts>` |
| Dev (backend) | `bun run dev` |
| Dev (frontend) | `bun run dev` |

## Do not use

- `npm install`, `npm add`, `npx`, `yarn`, `pnpm`
- `package-lock.json` — use `bun.lock` instead

## Where to run commands

```bash
cd backend && bun install    # API deps
cd frontend && bun install   # web deps
```

## Adding packages (examples)

```bash
# backend runtime dep
cd backend && bun add express

# backend dev dep
cd backend && bun add -d @types/express

# frontend
cd frontend && bun add @tanstack/react-query
```

## Prisma (backend)

```bash
cd backend
bun run db:generate
bun run db:migrate
bun run db:seed
```

Seed script runs via `bun prisma/seed.ts` (Bun executes TypeScript natively).
